verbose_text: Finally, ITZ has been reported to target p-glycoprotein, UDP-glucuronosyltransferase, and ERbeta, none of which are likely to mediate the antiviral activity of ITZ, because these are as potently inhibited by ketoconazole, which did not affect virus replication.
evidence: ERbeta, none of which are likely to mediate the antiviral activity of ITZ
